FBIS3-44263 "drafr019_c_94009" FBIS-AFR-94-019 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Jan 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Task Force To Inquire About Natal/KwaZulu Hit Squads MB2801064594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0551 GMT 28 Jan 94 MB2801064594 Johannesburg SAPA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Durban Jan 28 SAPA -- The task group appointed by the Transitional Executive Council [TEC] to inquire into the existence of hit squads in Natal/kwaZulu has begun its investigations in Durban. The TEC said in a statement on Friday the task group would continue to hear evidence and information, conduct interviews and scrutinise documents throughout the weekend and until Wednesday. It said confidential information may be given to members Howard Varney (031) 301-7572 (w) (031) 304-2823 (fax); Nicholas Haysom (011) 403-2765 (w) (011) 403-1765 (fax), or Col Ivor Human (011) 815-3141 (SAP) pager: 804-2777 code: 8113.
